<Author>ECCohen
<Content>Great location, nice hotel, noisy I'm very glad I booked a 2 night stay with Hotel Atlas after staying 1 night at Husa Via Barcelona far from the city center (misleading description). Atlas's location could not possibly be better - 5 second walk from La Rambla and right across from the Boqueria or food market. The only 2 downsides I can think of for Atlas are that it gets really noisy from about 8am on. The bell from the cathedral goes off and there is a lot of noise coming from the street. If you plan on waking up early, this should not deter you though as Atlas is a great value and an unbeatable location. 
