<Author>squirrel703
<Content>It's all about location We booked this hotel on a business trip to BCN and choose this one, because it is new and close to the Boqueria, the famous markets. We did stay at the Atlas Hotel for 2 nights June 19-21.They do serve complementary breakfast in the lobby area next to the elevator - nothing special - cornflakes, toast, cheese, ham yoghurt, coffee, orange juice and some sweet stuff. We never had breakfast, because we preferred the Boqueria for the tortillas and the atmosphere there in the mornings.The staff is very friendly and helpful. The rooms were clean and the aircon was very silent so sleeping was no problem. Of course there is noise out on the streets - but hey, we are in the main tourist area here and bars are all around.The Tapas bar, next door is excellent.We would definitively book the Atlas again for our next trip to Barcelona. 
