<Content>Barcelona is great We booked this hotel mainly because of its location, just a few steps from La Rambla. Its a bit overpriced, doesnt have minibar, restaurant, no breakfast and no bar..but somehow this was ok, just step outside and you麓ll have no problems to find something to eat. Quite noisy outside on the street. Lots of britts, drunk and carrying on late...not the hotels fault tho.Nice bathroom. They did not seem to use locks at the hotel tho. Once when we came back from a day out on the town we found our door open. Luckily noone had gone inside and nothing was missing. The door next to our room was also open, we looked inside and saw someones luggage and shoes but noone was there...the maid must have forgotten to lock the doors..Overall hotells are very expensive in Barcelona, especially close to the main attractions.Barcelona has lots to offer, its a very beautiful city and we will surely return. 
