<Author>JSammut
<Content>Great location, helpful friendly staff, Got back yesterday. I rated this hotel excellent for it offers what it claims. It is no 5 star in that it lacks services such as breakfast, pools etc but for those who only look for a good clean place to stay it is excellent. Pros - Very good location.Friendly knowledgable staff. Clean. Brand new rooms.Free Wi-fi though not very strong. Fantastic power shower. nice spacious rooms.Better than expected.Free maps in Lobby.Info desk well stocked with different maps( shopping maps, restaurant maps, Bus touristic maps) and other brochures etc.Cons - no fault of the hotel but location is near the churches and bells ring. Especially if you want a rest in late afternoon. Shops in area open shutters around 7.30am. otherwise not as noisy as we thought as it is just far enough from the Ramblas to avoid the noise on the main road. Having said that it is only 20meters away but round a corner. I would definetly recommend it and go there again. Liceu metro stop (green line)is only 30 metres away. Boquira market is across the street once you get on the Ramblas. PS. Do make a point of visiting the Magic fountain at Place Espanya. It is a fantastic free show. 
